1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the application of convolutional neural networks to customer products and proposes a novel convolution block to reduce computational burden while maintaining performance. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the development of a new model and optimization techniques for slim models. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of neural networks for customer products. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper discusses the development of a new convolution block for neural networks. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper discusses the application of convolutional neural networks to customer products, which may involve multimedia data.
